        "locked": false,
        "title": "Feature Request: Add workboard card delete/remove API",
        "body": "**Current limitation:**\nThe Workboard plugin currently provides no way to permanently delete or remove a card. The available lifecycle actions are limited to:\n- `create`, `claim`, `release`, `complete`, `block`, `unblock`, `reclaim`, `reassign`\n- There is no `delete` or `remove` operation exposed through the tool API or the management UI.\n\n**Impact:**\n- Archived cards remain in the database and accumulate over time.\n- Users who want to clean up stale/abandoned cards cannot do so without manual database intervention.\n- The management UI does not have a \"delete\" button.\n\n**Requested feature:**\n1. Add a `delete` or `remove` action to the Workboard card API (matching the existing tool schema pattern).\n2. Optionally expose a delete button in the Workboard management UI for archived/completed cards.\n3. Consider soft-delete with a garbage-collect period, or a hard-delete with confirmation, depending on the project’s data-retention policy.\n\n**Environment:**\n- OpenClaw version: 2026.6.5\n- Plugin: workboard\n\nThank you for considering this.",
